All stable phases of WO$_{3}$ are distortions of the \href{current_web_home_dir/A3B_cP4_221_c_b-001}{cubic $\alpha$-ReO$_{3}$ ($D0_{9}$) phase}. Based on (Woodward, 1997 and Vogt, 1999), the known stable phases and their approximate temperature ranges are: \begin{itemize} \item \href{current_web_home_dir/A3B_tP16_130_cf_c-001}{$\alpha$-WO$_{3}$ (1010-1170 K) (Vogt, 1999)} \item \href{current_web_home_dir/A3B_oP32_60_3d_d-001}{$\beta$-WO$_{3}$ (600-1170 K) (Vogt, 1999)} \item \href{current_web_home_dir/A3B_mP32_14_6e_2e-001}{$\gamma$-WO$_{3}$ (290-600 K) (Vogt, 1999)} (this structure) \item \href{current_web_home_dir/A3B_aP32_2_12i_4i-001}{$\delta$-WO$_{3}$ (230-290 K) (Diehl, 1978)} \item \href{current_web_home_dir/A3B_mP16_7_6a_2a-001}{$\epsilon$-WO$_{3}$ (below 23 K) (Woodward, 1997)} \end{itemize} ~ \vspace{-.35in} 
 Woodward notes that ``The transition temperatures display large hysteresis effects and universal agreement is not found in the literature.'' 
 In addition, several other structures have been proposed and/or found: \begin{itemize} \item \href{current_web_home_dir/A3B_oP16_57_a2d_d-001}{The original $D0_{10}$ structure (Br\"{a}kken, 1931; Hermann, 1937), superseded by $\delta$-WO$_{3}$} \item \href{current_web_home_dir/A3B_oP32_62_ab4c_2c-001}{The original $\beta$-WO$_{3}$ (Salje, 1977)} \item \href{current_web_home_dir/A3B_hP12_191_gl_f-001}{Hexagonal WO$_{3}$}, presumably metastable, found by (Gerand, 1979) while dehydrating WO$_{3}$$\cdot$H$_{2}$O \end{itemize} ~ \vspace{-0.25in} 
 \href{current_web_home_dir/AB3_mP32_14_2e_6e-001}{Monoclinic ClFe$_{3}$} and \href{current_web_home_dir/AB3_mP32_14_2e_6e-002}{CrTe$_{3}$} have the same AFLOW prototype label, AB3\_mP32\_14\_2e\_6e. This label is similar to that of \href{current_web_home_dir/A3B_mP32_14_6e_2e-001}{$\gamma$-WO$_{3}$}, A3B\_mP32\_14\_6e\_2e. The unique structures are generated by the same symmetry operations with different sets of parameters ({\tt --params}) specified in their corresponding CIF files.
